# One-line conditionals

- Omit braces when an `if`, `else`, `for`, or `while` body is a single statement.
- Keep the condition and its single statement on the same line.
- Use braces when the body contains multiple statements.

```typescript
if (!value) throw new Error("Value is required");
```
